  "local_port": 50426,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best books for bank exam?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a blend of understanding the concepts, practicing problems, and familiarizing yourself with the exam pattern. Here are some highly recommended books and resources across various sections that are commonly covered in bank exams like IBPS, SBI, and RBI:\n\n### Quantitative Aptitude\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal**  \n   - This is a comprehensive book that covers a wide range of topics required for bank exams.\n\n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma**  \n   - This book is particularly useful for quick learning and practicing shortcuts and techniques.\n\n### Reasoning Ability\n1. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal and Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal**  \n   - It covers both verbal and non-verbal reasoning systematically and thoroughly.\n\n2. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey**  \n   - It helps in building the foundational concepts of reasoning.\n\n### English Language\n1. **\"Objective English for Competitive Examinations\" by Hari Mohan Prasad and Uma Rani Sinha**  \n   - This book caters to the needs of English preparation with ample practice exercises.\n\n2. **\"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis**  \n   - It's a classic book that improves vocabulary and comprehension skills.\n\n### General Awareness\n1. **\"Manorama Yearbook\"**  \n   - It provides extensive coverage of current affairs and general knowledge.\n\n2. **\"Lucent\u2019s General Knowledge\"**  \n   - A good source for static GK as well as some current affairs.\n\n### Banking Awareness\n1. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Publications**  \n   - Covers all necessary topics related to banking terminology, practices, and the economy.\n\n2. **\"Guide to Banking General Awareness\" by RPH Editorial Board**  \n   - Another comprehensive guide focused on banking sector awareness.\n\n### Practice Papers and Previous Year Papers\n1. **\"IBPS Bank Clerk Preliminary & Main Exam Guide\" by Disha Experts**  \n   - Useful for practice papers and understanding the exam pattern.\n\n2. **\"SBI PO Previous Year Papers\" by Kiran Publications**  \n   - Solving previous years' papers is crucial for getting a real exam feel.\n\nIt\u2019s important to also keep up with daily current affairs, which you can do through newspapers like The Hindu, online portals, or apps that update daily current events. Regular practice with mock tests and time management during practice sessions is also key to performing well in bank exams.",
